name: Risograph of Cuban Boy
description: Three colour risograph printed on A3 (420 x 297 mm),180grm paper.

name: Espresso cups and saucers, set of 3.
description: Sold in sets of three these are vitrified porcelain 3oz espresso cups. They depict a dog, a cycle and a monkey.

name: Cuban Boy with meter
description:
Drawn from Cuba 1996. 
Images applied to 18oz, 53cl Porcelite, high performance vitrified porcelain latte mugs and espresso cups and saucers. 
The height of the mug is 15cms (6") high.
There are two designs, Cuban Boy  and Cuban Boy with meter.
They are packaged in a risograph print on to 120g A3 paper,100% recycled. The printer uses a stencil wrapped around a drum through which the wet soya ink is pushed and each colour needs a separate stencil. The ink is soya-based and contains none of the solvents that cause volatile organic emissions.
